<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Fire in vernal pool systems is not understood well historically. Although the likelihood of frequent fire is high in most cismontane grasslands of the state, the lower fuel volumes and the wetter condition of the plants in vernal pools with respect to surrounding grasslands may have minimized fire spread in vernal pools (Wills 2006). Late summer to fall season fire is likely to have neutral to positive effects on the native, seed-banking annuals and geophytes.</div>
