    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        
            <p><i>Lasthenia glaberrima</i> occurs in vernal pools within the Great Valley (262A), Sierra Nevada Foothills (M261F), Northern Central Coast (263A), and Central California Coast (261A).</p>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Central California Coast</b> (261Af). One stand occurs within Jasper Ridge Biological Preserve.</li>
        
            <li><b>Great Valley</b> (262Aa-d, Ag-k, Am, Ao-p, Ar-u). The <i>Lasthenia glaberrima-Lupinus bicolor</i> association occurs on vertisols of the Solano-Colusa region (Keeler-Wolf et al. 1998a). The <i>Lasthenia glaberrima-Downingia insignis</i> association occurs on claypan pools and the <i>Lasthenia glaberrima-Downingia bicornuta</i> association occurs on hardpan pools in the Solano- Colusa area and northern Sacramento Valley. The <i>Lasthenia glaberrima-Pleuropogon californicus</i> association occurs on claypan pools near the Jepson Prairie Preserve in the southern portion of the Solano-Colusa region.</li>
        
            <li><b>Northern California Coast</b> (263Aj, Al). Small vernal pool stands occur near Sears Point Ranch and Mount Burdell.</li>
        
            <li><b>Sierra Nevada Foothills</b> (M261Fa-b). The <i>Lasthenia glaberrima-Pogogyne douglasii</i> association occurs on volcanic rock of table mountains. The <i>Lasthenia glaberrima-Trifolium variegatum</i> association occurs on hardpan and volcanic rock pools.</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> All vernal pools in cismontane California are depleted severely in number and extent. Threats are primarily from loss of habitat due to conversion to agriculture and development. However, threats also include invasive non-natives, such as <i>Hordeum marinum, Leontodon saxatilis, Lolium perenne, Lythrum hyssopifolia, </i>and <i>Polypogon monspeliensis, </i>commonly found in this alliance. </div>
</div>

    

    

